Vladimir Nabokov





TO: THE LONDON TIMES

PRINTED LETTER1





Sir.—I find my name listed in the programme of the Edinburgh International Festival among those of writers invited to take part in its Writers' Conference. In the same list I find several writers whom I respect but also some others—such as Ilya Ehrenburg, Bertrand Russell, and J.-P. Sartre—with whom I would not consent, to participate in any festival or conference whatsoever. N